name: analytics_management_webproperties_list
description: Lists web properties to which the user has access.

accountId.description: Account ID to retrieve web properties for. Can either be a specific account ID or '~all', which refers to all the accounts that user has access to.

max-results.description: The maximum number of web properties to include in this response.

start-index.description: An index of the first entity to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: An opaque string that represents a user for quota purposes. Must not exceed 40 characters.

$block: A web property collection lists Analytics web properties to which the user has access. Each resource in the collection corresponds to a single Analytics web property.

$ul: **itemsPerPage**: The maximum number of resources the response can contain, regardless of the actual number of resources returned. Its value ranges from 1 to 1000 with a value of 1000 by default, or otherwise specified by the max-results query parameter.
**nextLink**: Link to next page for this web property collection.
**previousLink**: Link to previous page for this web property collection.
**startIndex**: The starting index of the resources, which is 1 by default or otherwise specified by the start-index query parameter.
**totalResults**: The total number of results for the query, regardless of the number of results in the response.
**username**: Email ID of the authenticated user
